A rushlight is a basic candle made by soaking the pith of the rush plant, a reed found by water, in fat or grease. They were an increadeby easy and cheap way to produce light for the average household. One rushlight burns for 10 minutes, and shines bright light in a 5ft square and dim light in a further 10ft 